---
title: Mediterranean Chicken Barley Bowls with Roasted Broccoli & Lemony Yogurt Drizzle
description: This bowl features the ancient grain barley, which has been satisfying tummies with its pleasantly chewy texture and nutty flavor since the dawn of civilization. Here, barley is seasoned with Italian herbs and fresh garlic to make a delicious bed for crispy roasted broccoli and juicy seared chicken. It’s all drizzled with a zesty lemon yogurt sauce for a simple, hearty dinner idea for the ages!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mediterranean-chicken-barley-bowls-3ff1cbd6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64761637fb53569c5a6229da.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mediterranean-chicken-barley-bowls-64761637fb53569c5a6229da
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 14 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 19 g
  sodium: 320 mg
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @barley{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 2 1/2 cups water (4 cups for 4 servings), @Italian seasoning{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. (You'll use more Italian Seasoning later.)

Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until barley is tender and liquid has absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}. (TIP: If you end up with any excess liquid, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if liquid has evaporated before barley is done, add a splash of water.) Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

In a small #bowl, combine @yogurt{4%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice (big squeeze for 4 servings), and a pinch of lemon zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. (TIP: If you prefer a less citrusy flavor, use less lemon juice and zest.)

Season with a pinch of @pepper{pinch}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; cut into bite-size pieces if necessary. Season with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. (Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning—we sent more.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir chicken into pot with barley.

Divide chicken and barley between #bowls{}; top with broccoli. Spoon yogurt sauce over everything and serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.